bug.short_desc: Wrong / misleading msgbox titled "Sending messages" when saving message as draft (Ctrl+S)

reporter.name: Thomas D. (not reading: volunteer year in Zimbabwe)

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

who.name: Thomas D. (not reading: volunteer year in Zimbabwe)

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 523981 screenshot msgbox 'sending messages' while saving draft
Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:2.0pre) Gecko/20110402 Thunderbird/3.3a4pre
STR
1 Create new message with Ctrl+N 2 Press Ctrl+S to save the message
Actual Result - for a second, we flash a message box titled "Sending messages" (how misleading is that!), text: "Status: Your message has been saved" - after that, we correctly show message box titled "Saving messages - the message title"...
Expected Result - don't confuse the user claiming TB has sent a draft message while we are only saving that message! - iow, do NOT show the message box wrongly titled "Sending messages" when saving drafts - "Saving message*s*" as a plural form does not make sense either (can it ever be more than one at a time?), should be "Saving message - ..."
